00:14:04,360 --> 00:14:05,120
Don't you need

292
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:07,110
Shuxuan paper for traditional realistic paintings?

293
00:14:07,110 --> 00:14:08,420
My father paints too.

294
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:10,310
He layers the ink strokes all the time,

295
00:14:10,310 --> 00:14:11,480
so he has to use Shuxuan paper.

296
00:14:11,480 --> 00:14:12,940
How can we use other paper?

297
00:14:14,690 --> 00:14:15,600
Here are the paints that you

298
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:16,860
prefer painting with.

299
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:20,860
Chinese-green, vine-yellow, and powder-white.

300
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:22,000
I saw the cranes you drew

301
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,930
at the shop.

302
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:26,160
You like to use lotus-flower mauve.

303
00:14:26,730 --> 00:14:28,120
My father likes that color too.

304
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:30,520
He doesn't call it the lotus-flower mauve.

305
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:32,930
Instead, he calls it Xueqing.

306
00:14:33,030 --> 00:14:34,240
The most interesting thing is,

307
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,560
the name he gave my sister

308
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:36,670
is Xueqing.

309
00:14:38,670 --> 00:14:39,910
Where did Mr. Kanyama

310
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:41,480
find such a shop assistant

311
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:43,030
like you?

312
00:14:43,390 --> 00:14:45,150
Actually, drawing a lot of cranes

313
00:14:45,150 --> 00:14:47,010
is always a good thing, never bad.

314
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:49,440
Just look at how well you look.

315
00:14:49,910 --> 00:14:51,200
The crane is a symbol of longevity.

316
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:53,130
How could the Japanese understand

317
00:14:53,150 --> 00:14:54,880
the delicacy of our ancestors?

318
00:14:55,050 --> 00:14:55,910
Am I right?

319
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:58,910
Young lady,

320
00:14:59,730 --> 00:15:01,860
you're really good at doing business.

321
00:15:02,150 --> 00:15:03,750
What price did he offer?

322
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,550
Let me see.

323
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:07,910
Mr. Kanyama said

324
00:15:08,030 --> 00:15:10,550
he'll only offer the best price for you.

325
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:13,440
Have a look.

326
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:16,210
How can I see

327
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:18,150
without glasses?

328
00:15:18,910 --> 00:15:19,630
Well...

329
00:15:20,030 --> 00:15:20,750
Alright.

330
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:23,670
Go back and tell Mr. Kanyama.

331
00:15:24,790 --> 00:15:26,240
This is the last time.

332
00:15:27,210 --> 00:15:30,260
I won't ever draw it again.

333
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:34,120
You are my lucky star.

334
00:15:34,150 --> 00:15:35,440
You completed my first order.

335
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,120
Your name is Shuhong?

336
00:15:37,150 --> 00:15:38,880
Yes, it's very old-fashioned.

337
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:41,680
It's not that old-fashioned.

338
00:15:43,120 --> 00:15:44,270
Do you really think

339
00:15:44,270 --> 00:15:47,120
my cranes are good?

340
00:15:47,630 --> 00:15:48,630
They're not good.

341
00:15:49,150 --> 00:15:50,360
They're the best!

342
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:52,670
The cranes are dancing.

343
00:15:52,670 --> 00:15:53,940
Red ink colors the clouds

344
00:15:53,940 --> 00:15:55,480
and deep green dyes the land.

345
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:56,910
It's as if the painting is alive.

346
00:15:56,910 --> 00:15:58,170
Who would have thought

347
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:00,440
that you understand my work so well?

348
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:10,520
The Captain of the Inukai Regiment told me that

349
00:16:10,520 --> 00:16:12,710
he was very satisfied with

350
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:14,620
your recent performance.

351
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:18,160
What's wrong?

352
00:16:19,270 --> 00:16:20,120
You have always

353
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:22,120
appeared moody lately.

354
00:16:22,390 --> 00:16:24,360
Tell me what happened.

355
00:16:26,030 --> 00:16:27,230
It's about my mother.

356
00:16:27,550 --> 00:16:28,280
Your mother?

357
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:29,280
Yes.

358
00:16:29,560 --> 00:16:31,090
I'm very worried about her.

359
00:16:31,150 --> 00:16:32,810
Her asthma is acting up again.

360
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:35,720
Is that so?

361
00:16:37,650 --> 00:16:39,640
My mother and I care for each other deeply.

362
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:41,790
At 17, she married into the Banner Battalion.

363
00:16:41,790 --> 00:16:43,190
Then she gave birth to me.

364
00:16:43,270 --> 00:16:45,030
Later, my father passed away.

365
00:16:45,510 --> 00:16:46,910
She raised me alone.

366
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:48,740
It was very difficult for her.

367
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:51,910
The close relatives of the Imperial Family

368
00:16:51,910 --> 00:16:53,240
suffered such a fate...

369
00:16:53,510 --> 00:16:54,910
It is truly saddening...

370
00:16:59,150 --> 00:17:01,670
Is it possible for her to stay in Tokyo

371
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:03,060
for a month or two?

372
00:17:04,240 --> 00:17:06,240
I know a doctor

373
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:09,050
who is good at treating asthma.

374
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:15,109
Tufang.

375
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:16,880
You bought so many things.

376
00:17:16,880 --> 00:17:18,490
Why? Are you treating someone?

377
00:17:18,490 --> 00:17:19,690
My mother is coming to Tokyo.

378
00:17:19,690 --> 00:17:21,550
I need to make some preparations.

379
00:17:21,890 --> 00:17:22,950
I'll get it for you.

380
00:17:24,750 --> 00:17:26,109
Your mother is coming to Tokyo?

381
00:17:26,109 --> 00:17:27,310
When is she arriving?

382
00:17:27,430 --> 00:17:28,830
Within the next few days.

383
00:17:28,990 --> 00:17:30,580
Laixi, the battalion commander in Shanghai,

384
00:17:30,580 --> 00:17:32,440
just bought a boat ticket for her.

385
00:17:33,370 --> 00:17:34,500
Where will she live?

386
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:36,810
Your mother is a princess.

387
00:17:36,810 --> 00:17:38,580
She can't live in a shabby place.

388
00:17:38,580 --> 00:17:39,400
I found a place

389
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:40,460
for her in the city.

390
00:17:40,590 --> 00:17:41,400
When the time comes,

391
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:42,590
you and Kaizhi can come and visit.

392
00:17:42,590 --> 00:17:43,350
Sure.

393
00:17:44,940 --> 00:17:46,740
Do you need to buy anything else?

394
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:59,520
Another new customer?

395
00:18:03,430 --> 00:18:04,320
Shuhong.

396
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:04,870
Yes.

397
00:18:06,390 --> 00:18:09,550
Did you say anything to him?

398
00:18:12,070 --> 00:18:12,720
No.

399
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:14,950
I didn't say anything.

400
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:20,110
Why does it feel strange?

401
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,790
Strange?

402
00:18:22,030 --> 00:18:26,680
He didn't even smile at me.

403
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:31,860
It made me feel like I owe him something.

404
00:18:34,460 --> 00:18:35,630
That's strange.

405
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:01,400
We're here, sir.

406
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,480
Thank you.

407
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:05,920
Good work.

408
00:19:05,940 --> 00:19:06,940
Nice to meet you.

409
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,160
This way, please.

410
00:19:10,150 --> 00:19:11,260
Watch your step.

411
00:19:13,770 --> 00:19:15,480
Welcome.

412
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:18,810
You must be tired.

413
00:19:21,030 --> 00:19:22,230
There are steps here.

414
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:24,000
Please be careful.

415
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:25,830
It's right here.

416
00:19:26,070 --> 00:19:27,920
I specially reserved a room for you.

417
00:19:27,920 --> 00:19:29,640
I hope you can rest well.

418
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:31,310
Ma'am.

419
00:19:31,780 --> 00:19:33,490
Please take off your shoes.

420
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:35,700
What is she saying?

421
00:19:35,920 --> 00:19:36,710
They have rules here.

422
00:19:36,710 --> 00:19:38,520
You can only enter after taking off your shoes.

423
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:40,720
Put them here on rainy days.

424
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:42,690
I don't understand a word.

425
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:43,880
This is the place.

426
00:19:43,880 --> 00:19:45,830
Have a good rest.

427
00:19:49,190 --> 00:19:50,320
Thank you very much.

428
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:51,920
Have a good rest.

429
00:19:52,850 --> 00:19:53,810
A guest is here?

430
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:02,110
Business is good.

431
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:04,640
Yeah.

432
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:08,440
Sister Yoko can't stop smiling.

433
00:20:12,590 --> 00:20:13,400
When did you start

434
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,930
calling that woman sister?

435
00:20:34,310 --> 00:20:34,790
My son.

436
00:20:35,310 --> 00:20:36,380
Give me some water.

437
00:20:36,920 --> 00:20:38,650
The journey made me so thirsty.

438
00:20:38,790 --> 00:20:41,000
You didn't drink any water on your way here?

439
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:41,970
I didn't dare to.

440
00:20:42,160 --> 00:20:44,400
You have to go to the toilet if you drink too much.

441
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:45,110
Let me tell you.

442
00:20:45,110 --> 00:20:46,550
The latrine on the boat...

443
00:20:46,550 --> 00:20:47,010
It's...

444
00:20:47,070 --> 00:20:48,440
It's uncomfortable to sit on.

445
00:20:48,440 --> 00:20:49,450
When I sit on it,

446
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:50,920
I feel like I can't pee.

447
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:54,550
You are really...

448
00:21:00,590 --> 00:21:01,790
The saying was right.

449
00:21:01,790 --> 00:21:03,320
Everything is good at home,

450
00:21:03,750 --> 00:21:05,680
everything is difficult outside.

451
00:21:06,520 --> 00:21:07,280
My son.

452
00:21:08,590 --> 00:21:09,830
Why don't I see a bed

453
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:12,510
in this room?

454
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:15,410
Where should I sleep tonight?

455
00:21:16,640 --> 00:21:17,770
I'll make it for you.

456
00:21:20,510 --> 00:21:21,110
Make it?

457
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:25,480
I have to sleep on the floor?

458
00:21:26,750 --> 00:21:28,280
That's the Japanese habit.

459
00:21:33,280 --> 00:21:34,440
Does Duke Ayakura

460
00:21:34,790 --> 00:21:36,480
own this shop?

461
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:38,200
No.

462
00:21:39,030 --> 00:21:39,640
Duke Ayakura

463
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,100
has hired a doctor for you.

464
00:21:41,350 --> 00:21:42,880
I can't bother him anymore.

465
00:21:43,270 --> 00:21:45,090
So I found this room myself.

466
00:21:45,510 --> 00:21:47,770
Besides, there are many Chinese nearby.

467
00:21:47,930 --> 00:21:49,790
It's convenient for you to stay here.

468
00:21:49,790 --> 00:21:50,350
Okay.

469
00:21:51,030 --> 00:21:52,030
Good idea.

470
00:21:52,790 --> 00:21:53,960
We can be at ease.

471
00:21:56,610 --> 00:21:57,400
Mother.

472
00:21:58,170 --> 00:21:59,860
I can't accompany you tonight.

473
00:21:59,860 --> 00:22:01,350
I have to go back to the team.

474
00:22:01,350 --> 00:22:02,160
Tomorrow, I have to spend the whole day

475
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:03,490
training with the team.

476
00:22:03,530 --> 00:22:05,200
School admission day is coming.

477
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:07,680
It's time for the carp to leap over the dragon's gate.

478
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:08,680
If it leaps over,

479
00:22:08,750 --> 00:22:09,550
it's a dragon.

480
00:22:10,110 --> 00:22:11,320
If I can't leap over the gate,

481
00:22:11,320 --> 00:22:12,450
I'll still be a fish.

482
00:22:12,810 --> 00:22:13,810
A chubby fish.

483
00:22:20,990 --> 00:22:21,710
Go.

484
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:23,600
Don't worry about me.

485
00:22:24,420 --> 00:22:25,940
I'm old.

486
00:22:26,130 --> 00:22:27,810
It doesn't matter where I die.

487
00:22:28,810 --> 00:22:29,700
Besides,

488
00:22:30,560 --> 00:22:31,510
don't you know

489
00:22:31,510 --> 00:22:32,840
how capable your mom is?

490
00:22:56,110 --> 00:22:56,750
Girl,

491
00:22:57,110 --> 00:22:58,110
are you Chinese?

492
00:22:59,270 --> 00:22:59,880
Come here.

493
00:22:59,880 --> 00:23:01,410
I want to ask you something.

494
00:23:02,030 --> 00:23:03,490
Well, I can't step on this.

495
00:23:03,610 --> 00:23:04,720
Come here.

496
00:23:09,790 --> 00:23:10,920
Old Lady, what is it?

497
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:13,160
Well,

498
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:15,250
you just called me Old Lady.

499
00:23:15,350 --> 00:23:16,270
Am I that old?

500
00:23:16,640 --> 00:23:17,400
No, no, no.

501
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:18,680
You're not old at all.

502
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:20,290
Call me Madam Liang.

503
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:22,160
My son is a military student.

504
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:23,350
We came from Hubei.

505
00:23:23,550 --> 00:23:25,080
We arrived here last night.

506
00:23:25,790 --> 00:23:27,970
I don't understand Japanese.

507
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:29,000
Look at me.

508
00:23:29,160 --> 00:23:29,880
I don't even know

509
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:31,200
where I should go to eat.

510
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,070
Well.

511
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:33,480
Don't worry, Madam Liang.

512
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:34,740
I'm going to ask Madam.

513
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:35,510
You stay here.

514
00:23:35,510 --> 00:23:36,480
I'm going to ask her now.

515
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:37,070
Okay.

516
00:23:37,240 --> 00:23:38,270
Girl, thank you.

517
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:43,750
Come in.

518
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,510
The food has been prepared for you.

519
00:23:48,510 --> 00:23:50,110
She didn't expect you to get up so early.

520
00:23:50,110 --> 00:23:51,720
Here, have some first.

521
00:23:52,110 --> 00:23:53,440
Madam will be here soon.

522
00:23:56,260 --> 00:23:57,020
Girl,

523
00:23:57,920 --> 00:23:59,310
the winter in Japan

524
00:23:59,340 --> 00:24:01,740
is much colder than the winter in Jingzhou.

525
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:04,030
According to bannermen's habits,

526
00:24:04,030 --> 00:24:06,640
there should be a cup of hot tea

527
00:24:07,050 --> 00:24:09,310
to moisten the throat before breakfast.

528
00:24:09,430 --> 00:24:10,650
Well, the tea...

529
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:12,920
No wonder they say bannermen are poor.

530
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:13,830
We spit

531
00:24:13,830 --> 00:24:15,290
in brick joints.

532
00:24:15,680 --> 00:24:16,830
When we buy some tea,

533
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:18,890
we display it to show off.

534
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:19,720
Fine.

535
00:24:19,830 --> 00:24:20,640
I'll go back to my home

536
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:21,880
and get you a cup of tea.

537
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:22,400
Okay.

538
00:24:22,650 --> 00:24:23,520
Girl, wait.

539
00:24:24,890 --> 00:24:26,350
Don't you Japanese people have a chair

540
00:24:26,350 --> 00:24:27,720
in your room?

541
00:24:28,660 --> 00:24:29,940
Tell Madam.

542
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,830
I'm old.

543
00:24:31,920 --> 00:24:33,160
If I always sit on the floor,

544
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:34,310
I can't take it.

545
00:24:34,830 --> 00:24:35,510
You should at least

546
00:24:35,510 --> 00:24:36,400
get me a stool.

547
00:24:36,550 --> 00:24:37,680
I'll find one for you.

548
00:24:37,680 --> 00:24:38,480
Thank you.

549
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:49,960
Do you adapt to the life in Japan?

550
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:51,590
Do you feel cold?

551
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:54,790
Please take care of yourself.

552
00:24:57,640 --> 00:24:58,510
Come in.

553
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:02,960
Japanese sounds nice.

554
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:05,700
But I can't understand it.

555
00:25:09,750 --> 00:25:10,790
Girl, thank you.

556
00:25:11,420 --> 00:25:12,200
There's no stool.

557
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:13,110
I brought you this.

558
00:25:13,110 --> 00:25:14,140
This will do.

559
00:25:15,160 --> 00:25:15,920
No.

560
00:25:16,440 --> 00:25:18,240
This is not for sitting.

561
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:20,270
She wouldn't let you sit on it.

562
00:25:20,270 --> 00:25:21,270
Really?

563
00:25:22,750 --> 00:25:24,350
Can I sit on it after she leaves?

564
00:25:24,350 --> 00:25:24,880
Yes.

565
00:25:25,110 --> 00:25:26,400
Okay, take it away.

566
00:25:27,590 --> 00:25:30,000
This old lady is really high-maintenance.

567
00:25:30,020 --> 00:25:31,350
There are so many rules.

568
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:35,350
Let me tell you, she is a bannerman.

569
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:36,450
A bannerman?

570
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:40,000
You are not from the same ethnic group?

571
00:25:40,020 --> 00:25:40,910
No.

572
00:25:41,300 --> 00:25:42,930
She's a noble.

573
00:25:43,370 --> 00:25:44,400
Maybe

574
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:46,000
her identity is Gege.

575
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:47,240
Gege is...

576
00:25:47,660 --> 00:25:48,320
Gege?

577
00:25:48,580 --> 00:25:49,290
What?

578
00:25:50,510 --> 00:25:51,640
They also have Gege.

579
00:25:51,770 --> 00:25:53,160
Gege is a counterpart

580
00:25:53,320 --> 00:25:54,320
of your princess.

581
00:25:54,430 --> 00:25:55,470
Princess?

582
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:56,800
She is a princess?

583
00:25:58,510 --> 00:26:00,110
So

584
00:26:00,510 --> 00:26:03,350
